hondo717: |cp||at|Good question.  I have a 4 loser hand, so 2@C is a possible opener. However, I do not like to open 2@C when my suit is a minor suit, because we are at the 3 level right away. Therefore, unless I have a real solid 2@C opener with a minor suit, I tend to open 1 of the minor. One of the worst auctions, for example, is 2@C-2@D-3@D. You are already at the 3 level, and you have essentially only made one bid. |
